(49, 415, 'Malinko Home Care', 'antony@liquidbronze.com', '', '91.135.0.169', '2013-04-03 12:12:00', '2013-04-03 12:12:00', 'Thanks for this really great post.  I''ve had a look at our welcome email and rewritten it.  We had a completely plain one - here are your log in details and a welcome one with a vague CTA.  I wasn''t ever really happy with this situation, but this post has got me to do something about it! :-)', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):850713010', '', 0, 0),
(50, 623, 'Iain Dooley', 'iain@workingsoftware.com.au', 'http://www.decalmarketing.com/adwords-book/', '125.63.55.9', '2013-04-03 22:06:00', '2013-04-03 22:06:00', 'Rock on, Chris. This post has some really interesting ideas. I particularly like that "personalisation" isn''t just about sticking some of their data in there (like Hi %name%! Thanks for purchasing %product%. How about buying something else?) but extrapolating that to provide them with some information that they''ll actually find useful.\n\n\nAlso, the thing about not emailing *enough* is really interesting. I always have a bit of fear at the back of my mind when I send an email - but really I should be creating email that I CAN''T WAIT to send because I know that people are going to love it so much hehe', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):851202182', '', 0, 0),
(51, 623, 'chexton', 'chris@getvero.com', '', '59.167.66.200', '2013-04-03 23:02:00', '2013-04-03 23:02:00', 'Thanks Iain for the kind words - definitely. All of the companies mentioned are pretty damn awesome at email, lots we can all use :).\n\n\nThat niggling feeling is pretty normal, it''s hard to always feel like you''ve written something you CAN''T WAIT to send, but that''s what we all strive for!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):851243821', '', 50, 0),
