(55, 623, 'inspiredworlds', 'matt.ho23@gmail.com', '', '122.106.52.186', '2013-04-06 00:20:00', '2013-04-06 00:20:00', 'Great analysis and some useful insights. Not emailing customers enough - I think appropriate frequency is dependent on the business and customer. In the case of a dating website, you want to be informed if someone is looking at your profile and wants to ask you out on a date. Time is of the essence! \n\nOn another note, don''t you think that the designs of the emails can be improved? I generally don''t like the look of any of them. Particuarly Zoosk one - I don''t like that bright blue colour. it looks cheesy. But I guess it might fit with their other branding. I do like the simplicity of the Badoo email with the Yes/No options.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):853610850', '', 0, 0),
(56, 623, 'inspiredworlds', 'matt.ho23@gmail.com', '', '122.106.52.186', '2013-04-06 00:22:00', '2013-04-06 00:22:00', 'As in the blue colour Zoosk might fit in with their other assets. I think linkedin does a good job with notifications about who has looked at your profile, friend requests, messages etc..', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):853611563', '', 55, 0),
(57, 623, 'chexton', 'chris@getvero.com', '', '59.167.66.200', '2013-04-08 03:14:00', '2013-04-08 03:14:00', 'Agreed, timing is dependent on a number of factors but it''s easy to miss those opportunities!\n\nI agree that the Zoosk email is fairly ugly and a large proportion of their emails have one or two lines combined with MASSIVE amounts of blue, a big footer and a bunch of other ''junk''. I definitely wouldn''t recommend their emails for inspiration - though it''d be super interesting to see if / what they''ve tested and how it''s performed.\n\nLinkedIn are doing a great job on their email at the moment. I love how they''ve started experimenting with the message you get when someone adds you. E.g. http://drops.getvero.com/image/0F0t1i1a1v3E. It now says "Good to find you on LinkedIn" from "Matthew Ho". It sounds much more personal...even though it''s automated. Interesting stuff.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):855831824', '', 56, 0),
