(68, 669, 'ish', 'ish.fuseini@gmail.com', 'http://ishfm.com/', '50.7.31.18', '2013-04-18 03:31:00', '2013-04-18 03:31:00', 'Nice work Chris!\n\nTypo "includsion" under the okCupid example.\n\nIn your email marketing faux pas blog post, you mention image heavy emails can hurt your conversion rates (I''m looking at the Warby Parker email).  Besides alt tags, what else could you do to combat images not loading?', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):866662943', '', 0, 0),
(69, 669, 'chexton', 'chris@getvero.com', '', '59.167.66.200', '2013-04-18 03:36:00', '2013-04-18 03:36:00', 'Hey ish - good question! It''s a trade-off I think. There are certain emails in which images are important: after all, it''s hard to describe a new range of glasses without a few images ;). As such I think the trick is to test what the email looks like WITHOUT images and also to be savvy where you can. Based on the initial screenshot I was surprised that WP''s email didn''t just use text for each of the titles and links (for the glasses), instead they were overlaid on an image. So, basically, using images WHERE RELEVANT is the key.\n\nI also think you might find this interesting (if you haven''t seen it): http://www.emailonacid.com/email-preview/mozify\n\n\n\nWhat do you think? Always happy to chat for hours offline! chrish@getvero.com.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):866665438', '', 68, 0),
(70, 669, 'ish', 'ish.fuseini@gmail.com', 'http://ishfm.com/', '50.7.31.18', '2013-04-18 04:21:00', '2013-04-18 04:21:00', 'Email on Acid image blocking is very interesting.\n\nI initially started with A/B testing image CTA buttons against HTML buttons. Results are still out but we''ll see what happens.\n\nStill reading and learning but I''ll definitely shoot you questions later. Keep it up with the great content.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):866686563', '', 69, 0),
