(75, 742, 'Peter Michaels', 'doddsy11@hotmail.com', '', '86.181.84.232', '2013-04-30 15:16:00', '2013-04-30 15:16:00', 'Another great post, Chris.\n\nAnd you''re right about that Spotify campaign - the 48 hour change you make to your account is designed to get you jonesing for the ad-free service. So when those nasty interruptions pop back in after a couple days... you go running straight to that sign-up button.\n(I''m betting 30 days free as long as you sign-up to a delayed paid subscription first...) Great tactics, but also delivered as a feel-good offer.\n\nDropBox have recently got right on top of their e-game too, these new brand designs are clear, informative and strike the right tone.\n\nLinkedIn kinda grind my gears with their subscription management - I prefer to untick as many of their options as possible as they seem to want to wade into my inbox every time somebody, somewhere takes a bite of cake... but Twitter seem to have the right balance.\nNice work!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):880477440', '', 0, 0),
(76, 742, 'chexton', 'chris@getvero.com', '', '59.167.66.200', '2013-05-01 00:29:00', '2013-05-01 00:29:00', 'Hey Peter - thanks for the kind words. Really interesting re: the Spotify case in my opinion. I''m a fan and it''s a nice little example of how the unorthodox can work!\n\n\nAgree with all of your points: either way these companies all have interesting email tactics and it''s great to see given they''re at the top of their game. Lots we can all learn :).', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):880903353', '', 75, 0),
