(263, 1554, 'EJ Lear', 'leare@totalinfotech.com', '', '67.167.136.252', '2014-02-03 14:02:00', '2014-02-03 14:02:00', 'I hope it works for you bro, seriously I just wanted to help you out, that''s the spirit that I sent it in, nothing more :-) I''m working on a giveaway for my own site right now so that I can re-launch my business.  Had a heart attack (at 41), depression that comes along with it, but thank God, pulling out of it now.  Took 2 years but I''m back to being excited about marketing again!!  I hope an A/Btest works for you :-)  you can get me at: leare -at- totalinfotech.com \n\nHave a great day and you have done a wonderful job at your site! (I should have probably sent something encouraging first) :-)', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1228840209', '', 262, 0),
(264, 1554, 'Brian Augsburger', 'beaugsburger@gmail.com', '', '75.118.173.202', '2014-02-03 20:34:00', '2014-02-03 20:34:00', 'Hmm, not sure about those changes, would be interested in the results from the testborderline "get rich quick". Chris is selling a valuable product here, not a "money making" course. Not sure I''d do business with a company shouting "secrets" and "more money now". Let us know how it goes Chris, I''m sure I''ll be proven wrong ;)', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1229343708', '', 261, 0),
(265, 1554, 'EJ Lear', 'leare@totalinfotech.com', '', '67.167.136.252', '2014-02-03 20:45:00', '2014-02-03 20:45:00', 'It''s basic copywriting 101, no one wants to ''buy a drill'' they actually want a hole in a piece of wood or metal at home.  No one wants to ''email market'' they want the results of successful email marketing which is more customers and more cash.  Benefits, not features :-)  By all means you can tone down the message if it converts better, the point was to appeal to what someone is actually trying to achieve.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1229358120', '', 264, 0),
(266, 1554, 'Brian Augsburger', 'beaugsburger@gmail.com', '', '75.118.173.202', '2014-02-03 20:52:00', '2014-02-03 20:52:00', 'For sure, I agree. I guess my point was you can be the infomercial screaming $9.99 drill or the professionals choice at Lowe''s. Good points :)', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1229367714', '', 265, 0),
