(283, 1772, 'Kapil', 'kjekishan@gmail.com', '', '202.177.218.83', '2014-02-19 02:05:00', '2014-02-19 02:05:00', 'Should every business have a blog? Absolutely and you''ve cited a few great leaders in Rand and Neil, both of them ooze authority. Gone are the days where a blog was set up for the sake of adding fresh content. We are now at a point where your customers turn to a blog to suss out your knowledge and the quality of information you provide. For example, Neil might only post once-twice a week on QuickSprout but each of these posts are high quality which generate social signals and links. Well articulated post!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1250949447', '', 0, 0),
(284, 1772, 'Matthew "Kaboomis" Loomis', 'kaboomiscopy@gmail.com', '', '75.132.4.242', '2014-02-20 22:39:00', '2014-02-20 22:39:00', 'Fantastic blog post here. \n  Can you possibly tell me the source of these stats you mentioned?\n\n\n61% of consumers have made a purchase based on a blog post.\n\n60% of consumers feel positive about a corporate brand after reading their blog.\n82% of consumers enjoy reading relevant content from company blogs.\n70% of consumers learn about a company through their blog rather than ads.\n\n\nThese are great and I''d like to cite them but need the source first. Thank you.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1253965053', '', 0, 0),
