(292, 126, 'chexton', 'chris@getvero.com', '', '59.167.66.200', '2014-03-12 22:44:00', '2014-03-12 22:44:00', 'Great point Jason. The trick here is to setup an email like "laurenm@yourdomain.com" that actually goes to a support desk, so anyone can handle it. This is a conscious choice and, if you''re in B2B, you may actually want it going back to the sales team member - but in B2C and at large scale this is a great hack to achieve the end goal!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1282095489', '', 291, 0),
(293, 126, 'JasonPeck', 'jpeck@hwy24.com', 'http://www.jasonfpeck.com', '173.79.117.160', '2014-03-12 23:41:00', '2014-03-12 23:41:00', 'Great idea, thanks!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1282157321', '', 292, 0),
(294, 669, 'Dmitry M', 'dmitry@safeharbor.com', 'http://www.safeharbor.com/', '24.22.143.95', '2014-03-13 05:43:00', '2014-03-13 05:43:00', 'Great post! \n\n\nI am working on a mailing campaign for a B2B company so our emails are less flashy and more content heavy. Looking at your examples it seems like it''s a good idea to stay under ~ four paragraphs. Would you say that''s a fair rule of thumb? \n\n\nAlso, the Hipmunk example seems way too short. There''s nothing about the company. If you are not familiar with the name you''ll probably think it''s a social media company.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1282463218', '', 0, 0),
(295, 669, 'chexton', 'chris@getvero.com', '', '59.167.66.200', '2014-03-17 03:17:00', '2014-03-17 03:17:00', 'Glad you enjoyed it Dmitry, thanks for the kind words.\n\n\nI would say that is a fair rule of thumb, most emails I see don''t exceed that. Having said this, B2B is a space where you can be a bit creative: people are more likely to read longer posts in the world of B2B than B2C so it might be worth testing out a few long form emails and seeing how your audience reacts.\n\n\nThis is a good point re: Hipmunk - it''s rarely a good idea to assume people remember who you are when an email comes out of the blue!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1287781616', '', 294, 0),
(296, 1735, 'Dennis, ListsUK', 'dennis@listsuk.com', '', '81.109.19.219', '2014-03-21 13:08:00', '2014-03-21 13:08:00', 'Good set of recommendations, thanks Chris. We''ve been running some tests with https://www.emailonacid.com/ - anything particular that makes you use Litmus instead?', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1294706117', '', 0, 0),
(297, 1735, 'chexton', 'chris@getvero.com', '', '124.149.182.142', '2014-03-22 03:11:00', '2014-03-22 03:11:00', 'Nothing in particular Dennis, Email On Acid is also great :). Litmus is just the tool I''ve used for years!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1295981774', '', 296, 0),
