(353, 2529, 'Sam at Feedback Loop', 'sam@fbk.io', 'http://www.feedbackloop.com.au', '173.247.206.210', '2014-04-23 19:30:00', '2014-04-23 19:30:00', 'I don''t think the the SouthWest email deserves A+, there are too many calls to action and they give the user too many options. Instead of revealing a bunch of hotels and their prices, they could just have something like "{{first.name}}, we''ve selected 45 hotel deals for you, click here to see them" and include a picture of a beautiful hotel. Add in concise offers for car deals and upgrades and you could also track what users are more interested in and retarget/optimise the offers later.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1352324457', '', 0, 0),
(354, 2529, 'Jarrod', 'jpurchs@gmail.com', '', '86.164.217.114', '2014-04-24 08:10:00', '2014-04-24 08:10:00', 'It''s very important to note that in countries like Australia, where anti-spam laws are quite strong, having "salesy" messages in a transactional email is against the law.\n\nif you want to send an email to a customer who has unsubscribed (for example, an order confirmation which is essential to your service to them) then you can''t put any sales pushes. Just information regarding their order.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1353095102', '', 0, 0),
