(369, 2605, 'Josh Kirschner', 'joshkirschner@gmail.com', 'http://www.techlicious.com', '108.46.26.229', '2014-05-06 22:56:00', '2014-05-06 22:56:00', 'I think you''re missing Alex''s point. You''re only seeing those G+ links above actual content because you''ve told Google those pages are important to you by circling them. Try searching in incognito mode (to block any cookies you may have, ensure you''re not logged in, etc.) and the results will likely look very different, with no G+ pages on the first results page. I doubt there is much, if any, real SEO value to creating G+ "doorway" pages.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1372765584', '', 360, 0),
(370, 2605, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '66.166.89.248', '2014-05-07 23:39:00', '2014-05-07 23:39:00', 'But why would Google show me a Google+ post that is nothing but a link to content above actual content? Why not use the G+ user''s influence as a ranking factor for the original post? My point is that building a large audience on Google+ and posting regularly is a clear advantage for small sites that want to compete with large ones.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1374321620', '', 369, 0),
(371, 2605, 'Josh Kirschner', 'joshkirschner@gmail.com', 'http://www.techlicious.com', '108.46.26.229', '2014-05-08 01:12:00', '2014-05-08 01:12:00', 'I think you''re missing Alex''s point and my point. Google is personalizing your search results based on what you like, visit, etc. You see Vero''s G+ result above Copyblogger''s because Google has figured out (correctly) that Vero is very important to you. No one else will see Vero above Copyblogger. In fact, I see neither Vero nor Copyblogger in my search results for that same term because neither is "important" to me.\n\n\nSo yes, if you can get tons of people to circle your G+ page then those people "may" see your G+ page come up when they do search related to content you have on your G+ page. But getting thousands or even tens of thousands of people to circle you is a daunting task and, even then, that number will pale in comparison to the hundreds of millions of people searching everyday where you really need to compete for SEO.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1374419118', '', 370, 0),
