(399, 458, 'Carmen Amato', 'authorcarmenamato@gmail.com', 'http://carmenamato.net', '186.77.207.171', '2014-05-20 15:38:00', '2014-05-20 15:38:00', 'I am just starting out but this is solid information with actionable examples I can apply now. Especially liked the point about mixing up content, not promoting discounts, but focusing on the CTA.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1395825440', '', 0, 0),
(400, 2703, 'Christos Vareloglou', 'christosvare@gmail.com', 'http://thedigitalrookie.com/', '89.210.178.200', '2014-05-20 18:12:00', '2014-05-20 18:12:00', 'Hi again. Great to hear that there is a similar effort from an other OTA as well. We are operating in Europe, USA and Asia. i just tweeted you my e-mail (christosvare@gmail.com) as i''d love to have a further discussion upon this matter.\n\nI''ve playing around a lot with segmentation(early birds, first time customer, high rollers etc.) but regarding subject lines, i''ve tested the following ones:\n\n1. Generic title(e.g. 6 great offers) vs generic title with a CTA (e.g. explore 6 great offers). Unique open rate: 22,58% vs 24,53%\n\n2. Short title(e.g. Join our contest) vs Long title (e.g. Join our contest and win flight tickets to new york,lisbon,athens and london). Unique open rate: 33,79% vs 32,28%\n\n3. Subject line with first name(e.g. Christos catch our new offer) vs Subject line without first name(e.g. Catch our new offer). Unique open rate: 26,63% vs 18,74%)\n\n4.Subject line with an emoticon (e.g. New offer for USA) vs Subject line without emoticon (e.g. New offer for USA). Unique open rate: 21,17% vs 20,58%\n\n\n\nI''d love to hear your feedback as well.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1396048302', '', 386, 0),
