(424, 2743, 'Bree Brouwer', 'breeleighbrouwer@gmail.com', '', '184.101.120.22', '2014-05-29 08:03:00', '2014-05-29 08:03:00', 'Hi, Christos! Thanks for leaving a comment. \n\nI think we''d need to see more info from your tests to figure this out. For example, we''d need to know what kind of GIFs you used. Some GIFs are static, while others are animated (which, I read somewhere, some email clients have trouble showing, just like they do showing video). \n\nOn the other hand, remember what Aaron said which backs up this post''s point; videos always improve CTR, even over images. The thing is, most email clients can show JPEGs and GIFs equally (once the email user allows images to be shown), but videos are still a whole other breed of marketing at this point.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1409649047', '', 422, 0),
