(449, 3096, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '68.63.199.168', '2014-06-18 17:25:00', '2014-06-18 17:25:00', '@disqus_VtbnUvHIHI:disqusVery cool stuff, thanks for pointing us here Chris.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1441939770', '', 448, 0),
(450, 3096, 'Barry Feldman', 'barry@feldmancreative.com', 'http://www.feldmancreative.com/', '99.116.20.158', '2014-06-18 17:51:00', '2014-06-18 17:51:00', 'Really great stuff. It''s great to see how the power of community is put in play by these leaders. It''s frustrating though, that almost everytime we see great examples like these they essentially come from brands inside the online marketing space. It''s time to see these lessons applied elsewhere. I know they exist (e.g. foodie sites, small business, etc.), but they''re few and far between in B2B.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1442004041', '', 0, 0),
(451, 3096, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '68.63.199.168', '2014-06-18 18:02:00', '2014-06-18 18:02:00', '@barryjfeldman:disqus Totally agree. It would be cool to see some brands start sponsoring communities they didn''t start. I think part of the issue is that it''s hard for most businesses to wrap their head around "giving." For those who do, there are massive benefits to reap.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1442030988', '', 450, 0),
