(456, 2382, 'bsjut', 'bjoern.sjut@gmx.net', '', '87.154.98.107', '2014-06-19 12:29:00', '2014-06-19 12:29:00', 'I don''t understand the perception that Uber is spending "almost 0 dollars on marketing". If I have a 20USD/20USD referral program, I''m spending very little money on traditional media costs, but I''m spending significant money on marketing if the referral program takes off.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1443673015', '', 0, 0),
(457, 3096, 'Joe Putnam', 'putnamjw@gmail.com', 'http://5northmarketing.com/', '70.238.203.222', '2014-06-19 15:55:00', '2014-06-19 15:55:00', 'I really like the focus here on community instead of content. Everyone''s been talking about content for a long time, but as this post points out, a lot of industry leaders are moving towards communities as a way to grow their brands further and not just relying on content.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1444059009', '', 0, 0),
(458, 3096, 'Zack Glascock', 'mzglasco@syr.edu', '', '69.46.225.194', '2014-06-19 16:08:00', '2014-06-19 16:08:00', 'Great post. Curious as a growth hacker at a startup how to build a community that doesn''t to many outlets at the moment. I am trying to create solid blog/community around technology being used for home automation. I would love to hear so techniques for raising awareness about this topic and get people to start chatting about what they are using in their homes. I also really enjoyed the guide!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1444077976', '', 0, 0),
(459, 2382, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '68.63.199.168', '2014-06-19 16:09:00', '2014-06-19 16:09:00', '@bsjut:disqus You raise a good point. They are indeed spending money on marketing, it''s just not so focused on ads/content/social.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1444079834', '', 456, 0),
