(472, 3167, 'Eric Peters', 'eric.peters@mendix.com', 'http://www.mendix.com/', '50.245.54.41', '2014-06-30 21:11:00', '2014-06-30 21:11:00', 'Really useful post! Will definitely put a bunch of these to work at Mendix. It''s mind boggling how bad some enormous companies are at making transactional emails user friendly and productive as a demand generation channel. I think email as a direct response tool is heading towards a spampocolyps of sorts -  one country after another -  making these behavior-triggered emails all the more important.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1462323042', '', 0, 0),
(473, 3167, 'Emily Esposito', 'emilyesposito@comcast.net', '', '63.226.248.51', '2014-06-30 22:42:00', '2014-06-30 22:42:00', 'I am bookmarking this post! I love how you use real examples with brands that we know and recognize. Also love that you use good and bad examples, and give us tangible ideas for how to implement these strategies ourselves! How about an e-newsletter analysis? :)', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1462453827', '', 0, 0),
(474, 3167, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '68.63.199.168', '2014-06-30 22:55:00', '2014-06-30 22:55:00', 'Emily Esposito Thanks for the feedback Emily :)\n\nWe talk a lot about transactional email since it''s such an overlooked opportunity. You can expect more on promotional email and newsletters in the future though.\n\nSpeaking of newsletters, you might find this interesting: http://www.nytimes.com/2014/06/30/business/media/for-email-a-death-greatly-exaggerated.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss&amp;smid=tw-nytimes&amp;_r=0', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1462471975', '', 473, 0),
(475, 3167, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '68.63.199.168', '2014-06-30 22:56:00', '2014-06-30 22:56:00', '@epeters1:disqus It almost seems like the bigger the company, the worse the transactional emails are. There are, of course, exceptions but most of the companies that are really killing it are small businesses that aren''t afraid to let their personalities shine.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1462473558', '', 472, 0),
(476, 3167, 'Emma Siemasko', 'esiemasko@grasshopper.com', 'http://www.emmasiemasko.com/', '72.74.246.210', '2014-07-01 12:55:00', '2014-07-01 12:55:00', 'Really useful post-- such a good roundup for someone who is putting together email lifecycle materials for their brand. Love how you not only showed good and bad examples, but dissected them on the page. Thanks for putting this together. Great insights for all of us.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1463272993', '', 0, 0),
