(577, 3632, 'William Boyo', 'willib0y@yahoo.com', '', '72.89.152.21', '2014-09-13 16:56:00', '2014-09-13 16:56:00', 'Chase and other banks have good reasons to make their emails non-transactional, as they want to get people out of the habit of signing into their bank accounts via email links in order to reduce phishing scams. Seeing that the average age of a bank customer is written in scientific notation, that''s not altogether a bad policy.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1587586954', '', 0, 0),
