(582, 4398, 'Jaina', 'jaina.mistry84@gmail.com', '', '37.131.1.155', '2014-09-17 19:03:00', '2014-09-17 19:03:00', 'Just like you have mentioned, working remotely has its positives and negatives. I''ve been working remotely for going on 4 months now. And while I do miss the office environment and even part of the every day drudgery of going to work, the flexibility of working from home is freeing. Though at the same time, you have to be very disciplined. It''s incredibly easy to just say, I''ll work from the sofa today in front of the TV. I''d hardly get any work done if I worked that way. \n\n\nI moved to Bahrain 4 months ago, from the UK. My company were very generous in allowing me to move and work for them remotely. So few companies would offer that these days, I feel. So feel very chuffed that they did let me. Work the same UK hours, which is actually better for me here. It''s been an adjustment, that''s for sure, but worth it.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1593489999', '', 0, 0),
(583, 4398, 'alan jones', 'alan@thenewagency.com.au', 'http://about.me/alanjones', '59.167.65.89', '2014-09-18 03:02:00', '2014-09-18 03:02:00', '"plant" or "planet"? either way, I wholeheartedly agree with your point. In fact, I''d argue we''re approaching a time when we stop defining not just companies but whole nations in geographic terms. Why must we be forced to share a tax base and a government with people we share nothing in common with other than locality? Why can''t I pay my taxes and have direct representation in a government-in-the-cloud that then negotiates on my behalf with the nearest providers of healthcare, education, roads, etc?', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1594077082', '', 0, 0),
(584, 4398, 'Ryan Collins', 'misslorettafishing@gmail.com', 'http://www.myfishingcapecod.com/', '173.48.34.155', '2014-09-18 13:31:00', '2014-09-18 13:31:00', 'I cherish owning my work schedule. Just had my morning cup of coffee by the pond near my house. Gonna get some computer work done this morning, then go to the gym. Get a bit more done this afternoon, maybe go for another walk in the woods before it gets dark. No anxiety and no stress means my hours spent behind the laptop are uber productive ... and focused towards achieving life goals that mean something to me. No busy work here!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1594529569', '', 0, 0),
(585, 4440, 'dprol', 'dprol@mail.com', '', '212.21.251.153', '2014-09-18 18:11:00', '2014-09-18 18:11:00', 'exactly! Love this post! Thanks for sharing! I totally agree, I''m twenty and I want follow your ideas. This Is The Life', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1594965476', '', 0, 0),
(586, 4440, 'Jaina', 'jaina.mistry84@gmail.com', '', '37.131.1.155', '2014-09-18 20:13:00', '2014-09-18 20:13:00', 'Really well put. Limiting yourself to a location in this day for business isn''t exactly a good idea, especially if you have aspirations for your business to be global. Location doesn''t matter with technology making it so easy to be in touch with almost anyone wherever they are.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1595166613', '', 0, 0),
(587, 4398, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '68.63.199.168', '2014-09-18 21:10:00', '2014-09-18 21:10:00', 'sounds like an ideal work day!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1595294049', '', 584, 0),
(588, 4398, 'Craig McGill', 'craig@craig-mcgill.com', 'http://www.contently-managed.com/blog', '199.4.27.122', '2014-09-19 09:33:00', '2014-09-19 09:33:00', 'Nice post. I wonder if it works better for people without children in some cases though. (I have to say when I did it with children it actually worked quite well but I know others don''t like the lack of routine.)', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1595982100', '', 0, 0),
(589, 4398, 'Vanessa', 'msjakubowski1@aol.co.uk', '', '109.144.228.202', '2014-09-19 10:06:00', '2014-09-19 10:06:00', 'I feel so lucky to be able to work from home, but I think its important to have good connections to friends and family otherwise you can go a little insane! I dislike office politics and horrible bosses so it works perfectly for me, but for many the banter of the office life are what makes work enjoyable. I totally agree that when working like this it does not feel like work! Best way of life for me!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1596018773', '', 0, 0),
(590, 4398, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '68.63.199.168', '2014-09-19 15:59:00', '2014-09-19 15:59:00', 'I have to make more of an effort to be social but the trade off is definitely worth it.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1596452437', '', 589, 0),
(591, 4398, 'nbevans', 'nathan@solariss.com', '', '58.182.104.59', '2014-09-20 05:16:00', '2014-09-20 05:16:00', 'I signed up to Regus business world gold card and I use their ThinkPods to do a full 8 hour or so working day. Then I retreat to somewhere more relaxing for the evening and continue on with a beer. Regus is damn brilliant for us digital nomads! I''ve been using one in Singapore for 3 months straight on just the basic Gold subscription and not once have they said anything about usage limits!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1597437176', '', 0, 0),
(592, 4398, 'Ryan Collins', 'misslorettafishing@gmail.com', 'http://www.myfishingcapecod.com/', '173.48.34.155', '2014-09-20 16:41:00', '2014-09-20 16:41:00', 'It is!  Definitely wasn''t always this way that is for sure....but now I wouldn''t trade it for the world. Nice post Jimmy!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1597920378', '', 587, 0),
(593, 4398, 'Abdiel Gutierrez', 'aage1970@gmail.com', '', '190.141.44.67', '2014-09-24 20:08:00', '2014-09-24 20:08:00', 'I have been working remotely for over 5 years and i have noticed that one bad aspect is the wages that are being offered to remote workers. If you go to elance or odesk you see jobs being offered at $.5 per hour. To me that should be a violation of basic human rights. How can you possible leave in this day and age earning a total of $4 USD for a full 8 hour day?', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1604143406', '', 0, 0),
(594, 4529, 'Jaina', 'jaina.mistry84@gmail.com', '', '37.131.1.155', '2014-09-25 16:23:00', '2014-09-25 16:23:00', 'Content is such a key aspect of getting email marketing right and it''s sad how overlooked it is sometimes. Think there''s a big misnomer that just because you''re delivering something to someone''s inbox, whatever is in it, they''ll pay some attention to it. People are so much more discerning than that. \n\n\nOff the back of content, knowing and understanding your customer is so key! That way you can deliver them content they want, when they want it.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1605397617', '', 0, 0),
(595, 4529, 'Andrew Tweito', 'consulting@funnelboom.com', 'http://www.funnelboom.com/', '172.6.231.65', '2014-09-26 12:44:00', '2014-09-26 12:44:00', 'Hey Jimmy... one thing I''d add to this...\n\n\nEMPATHY\n\n\nCrafting a buyer persona (or buyer personas) and outlining their common objections, motivations, and sales triggers is vital to creating an effective marketing gameplan... \n\n\nAnd obviously email marketing / marketing automation builds from that...\n\n\nIf your emails have:\n\n\n1.  Strong copywriting (probably the biggest shortcoming in the digital marketing world today)...\n\n\n2.  Leave your target audience thinking "I feel like he/she wrote this specifically for me" ....\n\n\nthen you should be well on your way to success....(opens, CTR, conversions)\n\n\nGreat post as always... Thanks Jimmy!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.77):1606809541', '', 0, 0),
