(664, 4686, 'Enguerrand Vidor', 'enguerrand.vidor@theiconic.com.au', '', '202.126.107.170', '2014-11-07 01:36:00', '2014-11-07 01:36:00', 'Very interesting. Do you know what Cross Channel Marketing software Airbnb is now using? (they used to be with ExactTarget and/or Responsys?) Also, is Vero collecting data and provides predictive analytics? Can you provide recommendations? How does it work (Rest API or Javascript snippet)? Do you have any integration with Google analytics and Mixpanel? Thanks!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1680658704', '', 0, 0),
(665, 4686, 'Andrew Gale', 'andrewrichardgale@gmail.com', 'http://hiandrewgale.com', '108.184.84.39', '2014-11-07 09:07:00', '2014-11-07 09:07:00', 'Hey Jimmy, Mix panel actually allows us to send emails as a result of those actions as well. It''s called ''Notifications''. It seems like it might be a pain to install all the events again through something like Vero when it''s already available on Mixpanel... Am I wrong // Missing something?', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1681006094', '', 657, 0),
(666, 4686, 'Jaina', 'jaina.mistry84@gmail.com', '', '37.131.1.145', '2014-11-07 09:07:00', '2014-11-07 09:07:00', 'I generally assume that too, but the amount of times I''ve had conversations with my parents asking, "how did they know?" when it comes to an email they receive - they''re genuinely astonished and slightly concerned!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1681006310', '', 654, 0),
(667, 4686, 'Jaina', 'jaina.mistry84@gmail.com', '', '37.131.1.145', '2014-11-07 09:09:00', '2014-11-07 09:09:00', 'Yes! Especially when it comes to services like that Airbnb offer, reviews are invaluable. A lot of places don''t make the most of the reviews they accumulate.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1681007451', '', 656, 0),
(668, 4686, 'Ross Hall', 'rossahall@me.com', 'http://www.aboutrosshall.co.uk/', '86.145.56.5', '2014-11-07 09:12:00', '2014-11-07 09:12:00', 'It''s an interesting application of event triggered communication and should be easily replicable. I just wonder how many will! \n\n\nThe price differentials on the alternatives are interesting, roughly 20% + and - (based on a sample of 1 of course!) Would be interesting to see if this is a common differential they apply throughout or if they''re picking up previous purchase patterns.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1681009968', '', 0, 0),
