(836, 4686, 'Farzana', 'fmwalji@gmail.com', '', '46.233.116.171', '2014-11-06 04:57:00', '2014-11-06 12:57:00', 'Is it just me or have they skipped on one of the most basic rules of email marketing and deliverability. Where is the unsubscribe link? If it''s hidden under the Email preferences link at the bottom of the email, it''s not good enough!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(837, 4686, 'Jaina', 'jaina.mistry84@gmail.com', '', '37.131.1.145', '2014-11-06 05:56:00', '2014-11-06 13:56:00', 'Honestly, I''m a fan of receiving emails that are relevant and personlised, just like AirBNB have done here, in terms of tracking your browsing and emailing you something relevant. However, I think that you can go too far and "creep" customers out by sending them an email like this. Perhaps they''re not as tech savvy and wonder how you managed to find this information out! That''s a big "What if" though. \n\n\nI''ve seen these sorts of emails go wrong, where one retailer sent me an "abandoned basket" style email, when I hadn''t even popped anything into the basket, merely browsed the site! Definitely something that needs a fair amount of testing. \n\n\nReally like the one big main CTA in this email. Despite there being other clickable items, the main purpose of this email is very clear from having that one CTA. Something that probably helps CTRs I can imagine.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(838, 4686, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '68.63.199.168', '2014-11-06 08:36:00', '2014-11-06 16:36:00', 'You''re right that there is a fine line between contextual and creepy. For the most part, I assume that if I''m logged into a site, they are tracking what I''m doing.', 0, '1', '', '', 837, 0),
