(910, 4726, 'Jaina', 'jaina.mistry84@gmail.com', '', '37.131.0.228', '2014-12-02 18:03:00', '2014-12-02 18:03:00', 'Think the most enlightening thing about Amazon''s approach to email is something you mentioned a couple of times in this post - it''s all about functionality rather than aesthetics. Which is good, but a little bit frustrating at the same time. Sure it''s great that their emails are functional and you get the information you need out of it, but a part of me feels that a company like Amazon could be pushing the boundaries a little harder with their emails just to make them *snap* a bit more. But I''m nitpicking here. Their ability to have such heavy data driven emails which are so well targeted and personalised makes the emails not feel like an intrusion into your inbox. And they''re never overly frequent either. Something I think a lot of retailers are incredibly guilty of. Amazon only ever send emails after website actions or perhaps big retail events, such as Black Friday. There''s never an email for the sake of an email.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1722258912', '', 0, 0),
