(984, 4398, 'Andrew Donnelly', 'adonnelly@mikogo.com', 'https://www.mikogo.com/', '80.193.64.131', '2015-01-22 10:01:00', '2015-01-22 10:01:00', 'I also work for a remote team where we have team members in a few countries and time zones. I myself have been working from London for just over 4 years while the head office is in Germany. Our company makes online meeting software for teams to collaborate together despite distance - so we talk the talk and, most importantly, walk the walk! :-) \n\nA few months ago I even went to Barcelona for a week and worked remotely while I was there. Why not? We''ve got the tools at our fingertips to enable such a remote working lifestyle. For those of you who are not able to work remotely on a regular basis but want to try it for a short stint, I wrote a post on how to make this happen https://www.mikogo.com/2014/09/11/work-remotely-abroad-week-barcelona/\n\nOf course it''s not for everyone. It takes disciplince, drive and self-motivation. You won''t get that same "push" that you get when you step into an office. And that''s very important for managers to consider as well when they''re looking to hire workers remotely.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1810748196', '', 0, 0),
