(1035, 5413, 'Jaina', 'jaina.mistry84@gmail.com', '', '37.131.1.23', '2015-02-11 20:36:00', '2015-02-11 20:36:00', 'It is GREAT that Ikea ask those questions on sign-up but even I, as an email marketing bod, thought it was a little much asking that on sign up. Why does IKEA need to know if I''m married?!\n\n\nThough I do see the point - the earlier you can get the information the better it will be for you as you''ll be able to breakdown and segment and target your customers better from day one. And they''re more likely to give you that information earlier on rather than further into the relationship. \n\n\nIKEA does have a leg up on the smaller business/retailer though - they''re a large, well known organisation. People generally feel better about answering those questions. They already have that built-in brand trust.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1848445848', '', 0, 0),
(1036, 5413, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '107.2.46.188', '2015-02-11 20:51:00', '2015-02-11 20:51:00', 'I hear what you''re saying. As Dylan mentioned on Growth Hackers, there''s quite a bit of friction.\n\n\nTwo points on that:\n\n\n1. It''s all optional once the person enters their email address. They can abandon the process at anytime and still get IKEA''s emails.\n\n\n2. Why not ask? It''s actually in the person''s best interest since it will make the emails they get more targeted/useful.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1848476078', '', 1035, 0),
(1037, 5413, 'Jaina', 'jaina.mistry84@gmail.com', '', '37.131.1.23', '2015-02-11 21:06:00', '2015-02-11 21:06:00', '"2. Why not ask?"\n\n\nAgree. Maybe IKEA could actually put that into why they''re asking the questions. They do just say "they want to get to know you better". Which is a bit vague and fuzzy for the every day joe. If perhaps they mentioned they wanted to make sure that you, as a customer, got what you needed/wanted from the emails (I was trying to figure out some wording, but my brain is dead!), maybe that would help cut some of the friction.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1848504354', '', 1036, 0),
(1038, 5413, 'Viva', 'viva0yue@gmail.com', '', '191.181.37.223', '2015-02-12 00:34:00', '2015-02-12 00:34:00', 'What do you do if you don''t have enough information of the user? such as age, marriage status etc. How to ask for the information and keep being informed?', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1848853019', '', 0, 0),
(1039, 5413, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '107.2.46.188', '2015-02-12 00:56:00', '2015-02-12 00:56:00', 'Really good question. There are tools that can help you backfill some of this data. Here are a few:\n\nhttps://clearbit.com/\n\nhttps://www.fullcontact.com/\n\nhttps://rapportive.com/', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1848881975', '', 1038, 0),
(1040, 4398, 'Lauren Mescon', 'lmescon@gmail.com', '', '95.97.35.16', '2015-02-12 15:10:00', '2015-02-12 15:10:00', 'Agree completely with you. I love working my business in my own hours and strictly online or through chats. I can be in Amsterdam, Barcelona or Paris, it makes no difference. I highly recommend it!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1849795071', '', 0, 0),
