(1046, 5413, 'Emily Veach', 'eveach@cbinsights.com', 'http://cbinsights.com/', '100.38.165.18', '2015-02-13 15:29:00', '2015-02-13 15:29:00', 'Thanks for the post, Jimmy. I''ve been enjoying Vero''s stuff lately. My question: What do you guys use to gauge conversion success from your newsletter, blog posts and other entry points? \n\n\nWe''re exploring our options -- and there are quite a few options out there.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1851794586', '', 0, 0),
(1047, 5413, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '107.2.12.250', '2015-02-13 16:05:00', '2015-02-13 16:05:00', '@emilyveach:disqus Really good question.\n\n\nWe measure newsletter subscribers and free trials using Vero. So when I send a newsletter, I can set a conversion goal (usually "Signed up for trial") and easily measure how many convert. It''s a little more difficult to track that across platforms and mediums. We use Google Analytics multi-channel attribution but are considering a more advanced analytics tool to supplement that (KISSmetrics, MixPanel, RJMetrics are great options).\n\n\nMonday''s post will tackle this to a degree - it''s a new way to think about and measure conversions. :)\n\n\nHope that helps. Feel free to shoot me an email at jimmy at getvero dot com.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1851854049', '', 1046, 0),
