(1102, 5464, 'Lewis LaLanne - NoteTakingNerd', 'notetakingnerd2@gmail.com', 'http://www.mynotetakingnerd.com/blog', '70.173.236.47', '2015-02-28 00:07:00', '2015-02-28 00:07:00', 'One aspect I really love about the "Did you forget something?" email is within the pretense of asking for reviews, they''re actually showing a list of awesome things to do there that perhaps you didn''t even know were available to do, thus enhancing your desire to get hit the road.  \n\n\nThis kind of email customization is definitely admirable and is something to aspire to. It would be very cool to see underneath the hood, how they gather the data, craft the emails, and deploy all this information in a timely matter and how a small business owner could do it for themselves. It''d especially be interesting to know if they were doing kick ass email campaigns like this when they didn''t have a giant staff to help take care of a lot of the details. \n\n\nThank you Jimmy for sharing this work of art. It is massively appreciated by the marketer in me. :)', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1879609921', '', 0, 0),
(1103, 5464, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '107.2.46.188', '2015-02-28 01:25:00', '2015-02-28 01:25:00', 'It''s a serious operation but it''s actually very achievable for small businesses with a triggered email tool (like Vero!).\n\n\nAirbnb does this too but not to the same extent ... another good place to get ideas.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1879698605', '', 1102, 0),
