(1107, 5466, 'Emma Cullen', 'emma.cullen@bannerflow.com', 'http://www.bannerflow.com/', '178.78.253.252', '2015-03-03 15:40:00', '2015-03-03 15:40:00', 'Brilliant post! \n\n\nI couldn''t agree more about setting a goal. To re-engage with someone can mean a lot of different things. You would communicate differently with a customer or prospect depending on where they are in the sales cycle.\n\n\nWhilst these are nice HTML emails, it would be interesting so see some re-engagement emails that work for those  you have personally been in contact with perviously but would like to get in touch with again without writing the ''I''m just following up'' email.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1885222888', '', 0, 0),
(1108, 5464, 'Anil', 'anilkbakshi@gmail.com', '', '196.27.77.56', '2015-03-04 12:09:00', '2015-03-04 12:09:00', 'Hi Jimmy,\n\nYou need to update your link to backlinko, as it currently goes nowhere!  \n\nNice article, very insightful.  What are your thoughts on how TripAdvisor measures the effectiveness of their emails (open rate/CTR/$$$)?', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1886732551', '', 0, 0),
(1109, 877, 'Jules Antonio', 'jules.antonio1989@gmail.com', '', '93.34.59.176', '2015-03-04 15:42:00', '2015-03-04 15:42:00', 'Don''t know if I''m going OT or not, but I''m using MailStyler and like it. I get templates that are responsive &amp; fine with every email service. Cool. http://newslettercreator.com/', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1887024218', '', 0, 0),
(1110, 5464, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '50.205.143.34', '2015-03-04 15:44:00', '2015-03-04 15:44:00', 'Thanks Anil, just fixed that.\n\n\nI don''t have any data on how they measure but given how smart their strategy is, I believe they increase the frequency for active users and decrease for inactive users.\n\n\nI do know annual revenue per user is a key metric for them. As of 2013, ARPU was around $12. That''s really impressive, especially considering Yelp''s ARPU is only around $1.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1887027137', '', 1108, 0),
(1111, 5520, 'dgfrancisco', 'dgfranciscorodriguez@gmail.com', '', '200.118.77.144', '2015-03-04 16:32:00', '2015-03-04 16:32:00', 'Ok, I love what you have been doing on Vero, I really do, but all your info its about to start good, the begining of times, but what happens when I have been sending good/bad/crappy/all kind of emails and after a year I want to start over and do better things for my lists, what are those steps?', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1887111785', '', 0, 0),
