(1116, 5301, 'Guest', 'anonymized-1894566850@disqus.com', '', '73.3.218.37', '2015-03-08 04:57:00', '2015-03-08 04:57:00', 'Lol at the Costco email. I call it "Vegas-itis"... when everything competes for your attention with bright colors and bold headlines and pictures.... and thus no one thing gets your attention. It generally happens when the marketing team doesn''t have autonomy by bored or control freak execs.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1894566850', '', 0, 0),
(1117, 4630, 'Michael Karp', 'michael@copytactics.com', '', '132.241.174.161', '2015-03-08 23:17:00', '2015-03-08 23:17:00', 'Nice one Jimmy! Good to see the Skyscraper Technique working out for you.\n\n\nI know how much time it takes to do that outreach, manage responses, etc. But that''s what makes it worth it when you get those kinds of results.\n\n\nWould love some social icons at the end of your posts, so I don''t have to scroll alllllllll the way up to the top to share your stuff.\n\n\n;)\n\n\nKeep up the good work man.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1895765388', '', 0, 0),
(1118, 4398, 'Nadia Kerr', 'keep_smilyn@hotmail.com', '', '110.175.1.186', '2015-03-09 09:28:00', '2015-03-09 09:28:00', 'Its actually quite frustrating how backwards about remote working most Australian companies are. Perhaps it a cultural thing in Australia or something else entirely, but most bosses in Australia still seem very anti-remote working or work-from-home, or at-least it seems very few and far between. There is even a lack of job listing sites for Australians to find jobs that promote such work conditions. Instead Aussies are faced to look abroad in the USA and UK where remote jobs are listed more freely and clearly. \n\nWorking from home / remotely does require a-lot of discipline and scheduling as it can be very easy to procrastinate, be distracted by non-work related tasks or slacken off. I personally loved not enduring commuting, being in my own space and own set time-constraints / schedule. ', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1896257491', '', 0, 0),
