(1188, 4398, 'Julian Staddon', 'bamheid@gmail.com', '', '86.129.228.127', '2015-03-31 14:34:00', '2015-03-31 14:34:00', 'I''ve been lucky enough to work remotely (i.e. at home) for about 6 months now. This has allowed us to move to be closer to support for kids. Mostly it is fine. You have to make an effort to see people - I pop out to a coffee shop to work sometimes and also meet relatives for lunch. Oddly, I miss the commute sometimes - it was a barrier   between the house and work - me time. But it''s good to re-gain 2 h of my life. Trying to get out for cycles when I can. Instant messaging is great for keeping in touch with colleagues and skype is a must for 1:1 meetings. Webex also great for meetings. It''s great to be able to play music too. \nI tend to use my laptop like a desktop while at home as I can use a big screen (when the weather improves - I''m in Scotland - I''ll probably venture to the garden :-)). \nTwitter is also a great place to keep in touch. I have a network of learning &amp; development twitter buddies. I''m at @julianstaddon if anyone wants to swap notes and working tips', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):1937987938', '', 0, 0),
