(1301, 5009, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '173.162.210.249', '2015-06-17 19:21:00', '2015-06-17 19:21:00', 'I consider that a commercial email but it''s probably a good idea to give it a transactional email. Amazon is king at this. I got into that a little more here: http://blog.getvero.com/product-loop\n\n\nAs an example, they ask for a review for every book you buy and they try to time the email based on the length of the book and when you purchased it. If it''s a Kindle book, they trigger the email when they can see you''ve finished it.\n\n\nThe emails don''t look/feel like marketing but they absolutely are.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):2084418717', '', 1300, 0),
