(1318, 6559, 'Peter Michaels', 'doddsy11@hotmail.com', '', '86.167.21.123', '2015-07-06 16:12:00', '2015-07-06 16:12:00', 'Great case study Jimmy,\n\n\nOne of the smart things Evernote are doing with their onboarding sequence is that "Tip 1/5" future pacing angle. By including their upgrade offer emails within the onboarding tips they avoid giving off a sense of "first we helped you, but now that''s over and it''s upsell time" ; )\n\n\nBecause they set the user''s expectations by telling them how many tips they''ll be receiving (5), they can continue to send other messages within the sequence, give the user the chance to experience the product benefits before the first upgrade opportunity, and not seem pushy when they do mention Premium features.\n\n\nGood to see them keeping their emails to one goal per email in pretty much each example, too (tips 4 &amp; 5 have multiple destination links, but they do at least make it clear what the reader can expect once they click).', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):2119638771', '', 0, 0),
(1319, 6559, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '73.143.155.213', '2015-07-06 17:53:00', '2015-07-06 17:53:00', 'Smart and straightforward. I put in a press request to chat with someone on their marketing team about how successful these emails are. I''ll update the post if I can get that information.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):2119831406', '', 1318, 0),
