(1323, 3632, 'William Harris', 'wm.e.harris@gmail.com', 'http://wheniwork.com/', '23.30.229.49', '2015-07-07 19:40:00', '2015-07-07 19:40:00', 'This is such a great resource.  My question then is this - is it better to send it from a different domain, subdomain, or actual domain.  I see a lot of emails come from something like xyz@m.company.com.  Our website is www.dollarhobbyz.com, but our emails were set up by another team before I came on board and they set them to dollar-hobbyz.com.  Which is the preferred way to send transactional and promotional emails of the above 3 methods?', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):2122041806', '', 0, 0),
