(1325, 6559, 'Susan S', 'susan@netfatuation.com', 'http://www.netfatuation.com', '125.239.30.0', '2015-07-08 16:53:00', '2015-07-08 16:53:00', 'I love Evernote and so this example really captured my attention.  Onboarding email #4, in the article, references a feature now found only in the new paid Plus level tier that was added a few months ago.  \n\nIt would be great to see how they''ve updated the onboarding with the new three tier pricing.  The emailing was such a popular feature that they used it as the enticement to get many long time free users (like me) to upgrade.\n\nIt was, to my mind, a brilliant move to create a new plus level in between the old Free and Premium model. Well played Evernote.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):2124144521', '', 0, 0),
(1326, 6559, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '73.143.155.213', '2015-07-08 17:55:00', '2015-07-08 17:55:00', 'I write about email marketing so I always need new examples. I sign up for apps all the time just to see what kind of emails they send me. You bring up a good point that I should sign up again a year or so later and see how things have changed.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):2124365715', '', 1325, 0),
(1327, 6559, 'Felipe Cardoso Barbosa', 'felipe.fcb@gmail.com', 'http://www.route.to/', '200.178.195.70', '2015-07-08 17:58:00', '2015-07-08 17:58:00', 'I was checking the emails I''ve ever received from Evernote. When I created my account back in 2011, they didn''t have a flow like this one (at least not for Brazilian subscribers). \n\nI''ve been reading and studying about onboarding for a while (since I''m responsible for creating the onboarding in the place that I work at) and I found out that the success depends a lot on business characteristics. \n\nI''ve registered to different competitors and they have complete different onboarding process and I''m sure they are being successful in their efforts. I know there are some best practices and emails that you just have to send, but finding the silver bullet seems impossible. \n\nEvernote now is a well-known company and it''s quite easy to get started. They also have a free plan that allows them to have a longer onboarding email flow (how would it be if they had only 14 days to make people learn and start using their product?). \n\nBut one thing that makes lot of sense for me are emails with tips. Maybe this kind of email can be created without overthinking about behaviors and triggers, but for companies like Vero, I suppose you guys take in consideration different behaviors to drive your onboarding emails, am I right?\n\nI guess more complex services need more complex onboarding that can look pretty simple in the eye of the person receiving the emails. \n\nI shared this article here with my colleagues made us think about our own onboarding process and what can we learn from Evernote.\n\n\n:)', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):2124376663', '', 0, 0),
(1328, 1174, 'Cioaca Virgil', 'virgil@senddelight.com', '', '93.119.226.244', '2015-07-08 18:18:00', '2015-07-08 18:18:00', 'Awesome post. In fact, we''re building a matchmaking platform that helps you find strategic partners and develop partnership a lot easier.\n\nIt''s not launched yet but you can sign up for early access. http://www.grewpa.com', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):2124462540', '', 0, 0),
(1329, 6559, 'Jimmy Daly', 'runjimdaly@gmail.com', 'http://blog.getvero.com', '73.143.155.213', '2015-07-08 19:08:00', '2015-07-08 19:08:00', 'Freemium vs. free trial makes a HUGE difference in the onboarding emails. Freemium means you have time to share tips and you don''t have to rush. Free trial means you need to get people going ASAP. We test a lot and are always updating our own onboarding emails.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):2124649831', '', 1327, 0),
