(1358, 1153, 'Harry Hawk', 'habs@panix.com', '', '24.193.120.179', '2015-07-31 13:28:00', '2015-07-31 13:28:00', 'Chris, this is great in terms of CTR -- more images, more clicks and some great hard data. But CTR is not CRO, and while you are are using the phrase, "increase your email marketing conversions" and it is a reasonable hypotheses that more clicks will yield more actual conversions, there isn''t empirical evidence of that from your study.\n\n\nFor a follow up I''d love to see VERO to reach out to some of those companies, where the data is available, and look deeper into the next level. How many of those clicks are truly providing an ROI.', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.83):2167145931', '', 0, 0),
