(64, 3, '2014-07-05 06:28:58', '2014-07-05 06:28:58', '<p style="color: #38454a;">If you followed the first step correctly you will now see customers'' email addresses and details on the<a href="http://app.getvero.com/people" style="font-style: inherit; color: #2dbcf0;">Customers</a>tab in Vero.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #38454a;">This is a great start but to start sending behavioral campaigns and to create meaningful segments, you need to track<strong>what your customers are doing on your website</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div class="video" style="color: #000000;"><iframe width="810" height="506" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;" src="https://fast.wistia.net/embed/iframe/92hxdgbow7" allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" class="wistia_embed" name="wistia_embed" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" mozallowfullscreen="mozallowfullscreen" webkitallowfullscreen="webkitallowfullscreen" oallowfullscreen="" msallowfullscreen=""></iframe></div>\r\n<h3 style="color: #000000;">Tracking an event</h3>\r\n<p style="color: #38454a;">In Vero, a customer action, such as<em>"Subscribes to paid plan", "Purchases" or "Logs in"</em>is known as an<span style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;">event.</span>You can track as many events as you want on any page of your website. Simply use the following code and change the ''event name'' to whatever you want to call the event.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style="color: #657b83;"><code class="rainbow" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;" data-language="javascript"><span class="keyword operator" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #859900;">&lt;</span>script type<span class="keyword operator" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #859900;">=</span><span class="string" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #2aa198;">"text/javascript"</span><span class="keyword operator" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #859900;">&gt;</span>\r\n  _veroq.<span class="support method" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;">push</span>([<span class="string" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #2aa198;">''track''</span>, <span class="string" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #2aa198;">''Signed up''</span>]); <span class="comment" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #93a1a1;">// Capture when a user signs up</span>\r\n<span class="keyword operator" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #859900;">&lt;</span>/script<span class="keyword operator" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #859900;">&gt;</span></code></pre>\r\n<h3 style="color: #000000;">Testing it worked</h3>\r\n<p style="color: #38454a;">To check if you are correctly tracking a customer action, open your website in a new tab, login and take the action you''re trying to track. In the example above we''d browse to the<em>Account</em>page.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #38454a;">If you return to Vero and head to the<a href="http://app.getvero.com/event-log" style="font-style: inherit; color: #2dbcf0;">Event Log</a>you''ll be able to see the event<em>Viewed account page</em>has been tracked.<strong>Success!</strong>You''re now tracking your customers'' actions in real time.</p>\r\n<p style="color: #38454a;"><img style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;" src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/track-actions/event-log-e8b318b90f7f54bc2bdeff24e9d93aee.png" alt="Event-log" /></p>\r\n\r\n<div class="highlight">\r\n<h5>DID YOU KNOW?</h5>\r\n<p>You can also use this code snippet in the ''onclick'' action of a link or button. Learn how in our<a href="https://www.getvero.com/docs/track-your-customers-actions#">Knowledge Base</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Track your customers'' actions (5 minutes)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'track-your-customers-actions', '', '', '2014-07-05 06:32:49', '2014-07-05 06:32:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=help_docs&#038;p=64', 0, 'help_docs', '', 0),
(65, 3, '2014-07-05 06:32:37', '2014-07-05 06:32:37', '<p style="color: #38454a;">If you followed the first step correctly you will now see customers'' email addresses and details on the<a href="http://app.getvero.com/people" style="font-style: inherit; color: #2dbcf0;">Customers</a>tab in Vero.</p>\n<p style="color: #38454a;">This is a great start but to start sending behavioral campaigns and to create meaningful segments, you need to track<strong>what your customers are doing on your website</strong></p>\n\n<div class="video" style="color: #000000;"><iframe width="810" height="506" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;" src="https://fast.wistia.net/embed/iframe/92hxdgbow7" allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" class="wistia_embed" name="wistia_embed" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" mozallowfullscreen="mozallowfullscreen" webkitallowfullscreen="webkitallowfullscreen" oallowfullscreen="" msallowfullscreen=""></iframe></div>\n<h3 style="color: #000000;">Tracking an event</h3>\n<p style="color: #38454a;">In Vero, a customer action, such as<em>"Subscribes to paid plan", "Purchases" or "Logs in"</em>is known as an<span style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;">event.</span>You can track as many events as you want on any page of your website. Simply use the following code and change the ''event name'' to whatever you want to call the event.</p>\n\n<pre style="color: #657b83;"><code class="rainbow" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;" data-language="javascript"><span class="keyword operator" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #859900;">&lt;</span>script type<span class="keyword operator" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #859900;">=</span><span class="string" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #2aa198;">"text/javascript"</span><span class="keyword operator" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #859900;">&gt;</span>\n  _veroq.<span class="support method" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;">push</span>([<span class="string" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #2aa198;">''track''</span>, <span class="string" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #2aa198;">''Signed up''</span>]); <span class="comment" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #93a1a1;">// Capture when a user signs up</span>\n<span class="keyword operator" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #859900;">&lt;</span>/script<span class="keyword operator" style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; color: #859900;">&gt;</span></code></pre>\n<h3 style="color: #000000;">Testing it worked</h3>\n<p style="color: #38454a;">To check if you are correctly tracking a customer action, open your website in a new tab, login and take the action you''re trying to track. In the example above we''d browse to the<em>Account</em>page.</p>\n<p style="color: #38454a;">If you return to Vero and head to the<a href="http://app.getvero.com/event-log" style="font-style: inherit; color: #2dbcf0;">Event Log</a>you''ll be able to see the event<em>Viewed account page</em>has been tracked.<strong>Success!</strong>You''re now tracking your customers'' actions in real time.</p>\n<p style="color: #38454a;"><img style="font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit;" src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/track-actions/event-log-e8b318b90f7f54bc2bdeff24e9d93aee.png" alt="Event-log" /></p>\n\n<div class="highlight">\n<h5>DID YOU KNOW?</h5>\n<p style="font-style: inherit; color: #0e0d0d;">You can also use this code snippet in the ''onclick'' action of a link or button. Learn how in our<a href="https://www.getvero.com/docs/track-your-customers-actions#" style="font-style: inherit; color: #0e0d0d;">Knowledge Base</a>.</p>\n\n</div>', 'Track your customers'' actions (5 minutes)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '64-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-07-05 06:32:37', '2014-07-05 06:32:37', '', 64, 'http://localhost:8888/64-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(66, 3, '2014-07-05 06:35:03', '2014-07-05 06:35:03', 'Now you''re tracking your customers and some of their actions, you can go ahead and start creating segments and campaigns. In this step we''ll show you how to setup your first automated behavioral campaign.\r\n<div class="video"><iframe width="810" height="506" src="https://fast.wistia.net/embed/iframe/6ki9uxaqw8" allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" class="wistia_embed" name="wistia_embed" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" mozallowfullscreen="mozallowfullscreen" webkitallowfullscreen="webkitallowfullscreen" oallowfullscreen="" msallowfullscreen=""></iframe></div>\r\n<h3>Getting started with an example</h3>\r\nThe following is an example of abehavioral email campaignthat is sent to users that<em>Sign up</em>to our fictional website, TravelWorld. It is sent 45 minutes after they signup and only if they haven''t yet<em>Searched a hotel.</em>\r\n\r\nThis guide should give you a good base for kicking off your first campaign. You can read the individual sections of this docs guide to get can get many more details on how to create<a href="https://www.getvero.com/docs/newsletter-email-campaigns">Newsletters</a>, a<a href="https://www.getvero.com/docs/transactional-email-campaigns">Transactional</a>email or get even more information on how to create a<a href="https://www.getvero.com/docs/behavioral-email-campaigns">Behavioral</a>campaign like this one.\r\n<h3>Create a new automated campaign</h3>\r\nGo to the<a href="http://app.getvero.com/campaigns">Campaign</a>menu item and select ''New Automated Campaign'' from the top right hand menu.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/create-email/new-automated-campaign-74a96906a84fb7083117b5f4c1508741.png" alt="New-automated-campaign" />\r\n<h3>Choose who to target and when to send your email</h3>\r\nCreating an email is done on the one simple to use screen. You can save a draft at any time. The first step is to select when you want to send your automated campaign.\r\n\r\nIn this example we''re going to call our email campaign "Welcome to TravelWorld" and send an email 45 minutes after someone<em>Signs up</em>(an event we tracked in step two) to our website.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/create-email/welcome-email-4ec44c4a95a4da5caf3f6d5eb1166fc3.png" alt="Welcome-email" />\r\n\r\nYou can also see that we''ve set a filter to ensure the customer only ever gets this email if they aren''t already in the segment<em>Searched for a hotel.</em>\r\n<div class="highlight">\r\n<h5>DID YOU KNOW?</h5>Segments allow you to name groups of your customers based on their attributes or the actions they''ve taken in the past. Learn how to<a href="https://www.getvero.com/docs/create-a-segment">create your first segment</a>here.\r\n\r\nIn this example,<em>Searched for hotel</em>is a segment that contains any customer that has taken the action<em>Search for hotel</em>at least once.</div>\r\n<h3>Write some email copy</h3>\r\nScroll further down the page and the next step is to write your actual email copy. Here''s an example of an email that uses basic rich text (it doesn''t use a HTML template):<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/create-email/email-copy-5eab76f38766e5819c88fd32642212b5.png" alt="Email-copy" />\r\n<h3>Send yourself a preview</h3>\r\nOnce you''re happy with your email, hit the "Save campaign" button at the bottom.\r\n\r\nYou will be taken to the Campaign Snapshot. To send yourself a preview of your campaign, select<em>Actions &gt; Preview via email</em>and enter your email address.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/create-email/preview-email-2be1b80881151566a20ad96683837b8e.png" alt="Preview-email" />\r\n\r\nA few moments later your email will arrive in your inbox, just as your customer would see it:<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/create-email/preview-in-email-bbe7ee265114a6f24ce140c41de40d7b.png" alt="Preview-in-email" />\r\n<h3>Go live!</h3>\r\nYou can make more changes to your email as you need to. Once you are happy, head to<a href="http://app.getvero.com/campaigns">Campaigns</a>dashboard and select the<em>Draft</em>button next to your finalized email. Choose the ''Launch'' option and you will be taken to a final confirmation screen.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/create-email/launch-b619cf72c293ef04e1ba3f007da5a8c0.png" alt="Launch" />\r\n\r\nOn the launch screen you''ll be given a summary of the campaign and how it is targeting. You''ll also see a count of any customers that have triggered the action (that is<em>Signs up,</em>in this case) within the last 45 minutes.\r\n\r\nYou can choose to queue up an email for these people if you want. Note that their email will be queued and the filters (Not in segment<em>Searched hotel</em>) will still be evaluated before the email goes out.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/create-email/launch-the-campaign-c77defc305c647b6d743220b3d511da5.png" alt="Launch-the-campaign" />\r\n<h3>Testing it worked</h3>\r\nTo check if your emails are going out, open Vero and head to the<a href="http://app.getvero.com/email-log">Email Log</a>. As customers take the action that triggers your automated campaign, you''ll be able to see the email go out in real time.\r\n\r\nIn the example above we can see when a customer receives our email<em>[Activation] Welcome to TravelWorld.</em><img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/create-email/email-log-da5bd78a5a409f762559c037cbdfe629.png" alt="Email-log" />\r\n<div class="highlight"><h5>DID YOU KNOW?</h5>\r\nYou can also troubleshoot when an email<em>fails</em>to send.\r\n\r\nTo do so, head to yourEvent Logand find a customer that has taken the action that triggers your automated campaign. In this example that is the event<em>Signs up.</em>\r\n\r\nOn the right hand side hit ''Show details''. This will detailallof the campaigns that were and were not triggered when this action took place and why. You can quickly and easily see which condition is failing or whether there is an issue with your campaign. at least once.</div>', 'Create an email campaign (10 minutes)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'create-an-email-campaign', '', '', '2014-07-07 06:46:51', '2014-07-07 06:46:51', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=help_docs&#038;p=66', 0, 'help_docs', '', 0),
