(71, 3, '2014-07-05 06:43:37', '2014-07-05 06:43:37', '<p>Segments are groups of users. The most important thing to know about segments is that they are<span>dynamic</span>- they are always up to date.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="video"><iframe width="810" height="506" src="https://fast.wistia.net/embed/iframe/4d3sb54idp" allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" class="wistia_embed" name="wistia_embed" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" mozallowfullscreen="mozallowfullscreen" webkitallowfullscreen="webkitallowfullscreen" oallowfullscreen="" msallowfullscreen=""></iframe></div>\r\n<h3>Create a new segment</h3>\r\n<p>Go to the<a href="http://app.getvero.com/segments">Segments</a>menu item and select ''New Segment'' from the top right hand menu.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/segments/new-c4bacf96fca6ebb436acc7265c666597.png" alt="New" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Define your segment using conditions</h3>\r\n<p>There are a range of filters you can use to define what customer attributes and actions define a segment. In the example below, we''ve created a segment called<em>Loyal US Customers</em>that is made up of customers with the user property<em>country</em>equal to<span>US</span>that have previously triggered the event<em>Completes checkout</em>at least<span>three times.</span><img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/segments/loyal-customers-108e1bdb1fba4151f370de14ec002400.png" alt="Loyal-customers" /></p>\r\n\r\n<div class="did-you-know">\r\n<h5>DID YOU KNOW?</h5>\r\n<p>User properties are individual values associated with each customer. You can track as many user properties as you''d like. Common examples include<em>first name, last_name, country, language</em>and so on.</p>\r\n<p>You can learn more about<a href="https://www.getvero.com/knowledge-base#/questions/50506-Identifying-Users">tracking user properties</a>in our Knowledge Base.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Putting segments to use</h3>\r\n<p>Segments are used to create and send email campaigns.</p>\r\n<p>When creating a<span>newsletter</span>campaign you use segments to determine who to send to. Here''s an example. In this case we''re targeting all<em>Loyal US Customers</em>that are not<em>New Yorkers.</em><img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/segments/newsletter-d1911efe98ebf846351e1ed71ff153cb.png" alt="Newsletter" /></p>\r\n<p>You also use segments when creating automated campaigns to target who gets your campaign and when. As shown in step three,<a href="https://www.getvero.com/docs/create-an-email-campaign">creating an email campaign</a>, you might create a welcome email that is only sent to customers that have not yet started using your website:<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/segments/automated-34df11f6f8f2821659bca2db06c522aa.png" alt="Automated" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Viewing customers in a segment</h3>\r\n<p>After you save a segment you can view all of the customers matching the conditions of that segment by clicking selecting ''View users'' when editing the segment.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/segments/view-users-1e0cebca52577d7ebeb2a7dcc517c0aa.png" alt="View-users" /></p>', 'Create a segment', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'create-a-segment', '', '', '2015-01-29 04:35:53', '2015-01-29 04:35:53', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=help_docs&#038;p=71', 0, 'help_docs', '', 0),
(72, 3, '2014-07-05 06:44:34', '2014-07-05 06:44:34', 'Newsletter campaigns are marketing emails that are sent to a specific group of customers at aspecific time.They are considered one-to-many emails, in that you are emailing to a number of people at once.\r\n<h3>Creating a newsletter</h3>\r\nTo create a newsletter, select the<em>Newsletters</em>menu item in Vero and select ''New newsletter'' at the top right.\r\n\r\nThe first step is to name your newsletter. This can be anything you want.\r\n<div class="did-you-know">\r\n<div class="highlight"><h5>DID YOU KNOW?</h5>\r\nWhen you have automated UTM tagging turned on (which you can read about<a href="https://www.getvero.com/knowledge-base#/questions/71767-How-do-I-track-UTM-codes-on-landing-pages-automatically">here</a>) the title of your campaign will be used as the utm_campaign parameter, which is publicly visible in your URLs.</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Targeting who to send to</h3>\r\nThe second step is to select the segments you want to target with your newsletter. Vero does the hard work to determine the unique users to send to based on the segments you select.\r\n\r\nIn the example below, customers that are in the segment<em>Paying customers</em>but not in the segment<em>Recent visitors</em>would receive this email.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/emails/newsletters-targeting-74b2c012cfa3ec2426efeb3460a882d0.png" alt="Newsletters-targeting" />\r\n<h3>AND vs. ANY</h3>\r\nConditions in theANDarea mustallbe satisfied before the email is sent.\r\n\r\nFor example, if a customer had to be<em>in the segment ''Loyal Customers''</em>AND<em>in the segment ''US Customers''</em>the email would only be sent if they were in both segments at the same time.\r\n\r\nIn contrast, conditions in theANYdo notallhave to be satisifed at once. Onlyonecondition must be satisfied for the email to send.\r\n\r\nAs in our example above, if a customer matchesANYof the conditions<em>is in the segment ''US Customers''</em>or<em>in the segment ''AU Customers''</em>the email will be sent if the customer matches either of these conditions.\r\n<h3>Defining your email content</h3>\r\nWhen actually writing your email our WYSWIG editor makes it easy to write your email just as your customers will see it. The WYSIWIG editor includes tools to upload images and manipulate your text. You can also select the<em>HTML</em>button to edit the raw HTML of your email body.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/emails/content-64a90bd1034ab007f582ed4571fd5941.png" alt="Content" />\r\n<div class="did-you-know">\r\n<div class="highlight"><h5>DID YOU KNOW?</h5>\r\nYou can also use templates to create more complex campaigns. If you want to use a HTML template read the section on<a href="https://www.getvero.com/docs/html-email-templates">using HTML templates</a>.</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nOur email campaigns use a templating language called<a href="https://github.com/Shopify/liquid/wiki/Liquid-for-Designers">Liquid</a>that allows you to insert dynamic content and even do complex math and logic.\r\n\r\nTo make it easier to get started, there is a series of quicklinks on the right hand side that allow you to insert frequently used dynamic variables such as unsubscribe links or customer properties. Here''s an example of inserting an unsubscribe link.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/emails/dynamic-tags-71683b89e00d6bdb90fbfd88f1446098.png" alt="Dynamic-tags" />\r\n\r\nClicking this will insert the value into the content editor at the point of your cursor.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/emails/unsubscribe-link-content-9ba7b674740feb1cace1ac9ecf4a4b19.png" alt="Unsubscribe-link-content" />\r\n\r\nIt''s that simple to insert dynamic variables.\r\n<h3>Adding a plain text version</h3>\r\nMost email clients now use HTML to display emails however there are customers that will have HTML email turned off. It is best practice to define a ''plain text'' version of your email content so that these customers have a better experience.\r\n\r\nTo define a plain text version of your content in Vero, select the<em>plain text</em>tab above the WYSIWIG editor.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/emails/plain-text-acdfb99d0b426384266b44b9b72f15dd.png" alt="Plain-text" />\r\n\r\nYou can now define the plain text version of your email. To make life easy, you can select theRe-generate plain text version.This will create a plain text version based on the content you have defined, using best practice. This includes ensuring the plain text version is the correct character width.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/emails/re-generate-2d3b16221cc3b6ed2fe504fec03f0b91.png" alt="Re-generate" />\r\n\r\nNote:The<em>Re-generate plain text version button</em>will only display after you have saved a draft of your newsletter.\r\n<h3>Tracking your email</h3>\r\nAll campaigns will, by default, track opens and clicks. You can turn this off if you need to (though we''d strongly advise against it).\r\n\r\nFor each campaign, you can also select an event as a conversion activity. When a customer receives your email and takes this action afterward, Vero will automatically record this as a conversion.\r\n\r\nDefining a conversion event is as simple as selecting one of your customer actions from the dropdown in the tracking section:<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/emails/tracking-3ffc926d3a6e71d598f4956c9f1504ea.png" alt="Tracking" />\r\n<div class="did-you-know">\r\n<div class="highlight"><h5>DID YOU KNOW?</h5>\r\nIf you have defined a tracking event, conversions will be reported automatically. Learn more about<a href="https://www.getvero.com/docs/reporting">tracking and reporting</a>with Vero.</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Scheduling your newsletter</h3>\r\nOnce you are happy with your email scroll to the bottom and select ''Save draft newsletter''. This will save adraftof your newsletter. Itwill notbe sent at this point.\r\n\r\nYou will be taken back to the newsletters dashboard where you will see your draft campaign. Next to the newsletter you''ve created, select<em>Actions &gt; Schedule</em>to bring up the scheduling menu.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/emails/scheduling-771743fd829eadb446d5c94a19be57e2.png" alt="Scheduling" />\r\n\r\nThe scheduling menu will tell you the total number of customers you are about to email. You can choose to send the email immediately or to schedule it at a time in the future.\r\n\r\nIf you schedule the campaign for a time in the future you can choose the timezone to schedule the campaign in and use the calendar icon to schedule the date:<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/emails/scheduling-date-1b65450a9ea2df8c65d15e9ddf7a0c22.png" alt="Scheduling-date" />...and the time:<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/emails/scheduling-time-6a9cdbc030dad85468622fb63db06445.png" alt="Scheduling-time" />Note that the date and time is in thetimezone that you have selected.', 'Newsletter Email Campaigns', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'newsletter-email-campaigns', '', '', '2014-07-05 06:46:22', '2014-07-05 06:46:22', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=help_docs&#038;p=72', 0, 'help_docs', '', 0),
(73, 3, '2014-07-05 06:48:27', '2014-07-05 06:48:27', '<p>Behavioral emails are marketing emails that are automatically sent to customers when they meet certain conditions</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Creating a behavioral email</h3>\r\n<p>Creating a behavioral email is the same as<a href="https://www.getvero.com/docs/newsletter-email-campaigns">creating a newsletter</a>. The only difference is the targeting.</p>\r\n<p>Newsletters are<span>one-to-many</span>whilst behavioral emails are<span>one-to-one.</span>Each individual email is sent at exactly the right time: as soon as your customers meet the conditions you''ve defined.</p>\r\n<p>The following is an example of an email that is sent to customers five days after they sign up if they have not yet searched for a hotel and are either in the US or Australia.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/emails/behavioral-email-targeting-fa71ad2ae8207ef12c18b9a387cd15bc.png" alt="Behavioral-email-targeting" /></p>\r\n\r\n<div class="highlight"><h5>DID YOU KNOW?</h5>\r\n<p>Behavioral emails are marketing emails so they respect unsubscribes. If a customer has clicked any of your unsubscribe links they won''t receive your behavioral emails. If you are sending a notification, such as a<em>password reset</em>email, use<a href="https://www.getvero.com/docs/transactional-email-campaigns">Transactional Emails</a>.</p></div>\r\n<h3>AND vs. ANY</h3>\r\n<p>Conditions in the<span>AND</span>area must<span>all</span>be satisfied before the email is sent.</p>\r\n<p>For example, if a customer had to be<em>in the segment ''Loyal Customers''</em><span>AND</span><em>in the segment ''US Customers''</em>the email would only be sent if they were in both segments at the same time.</p>\r\n<p>In contrast, conditions in the<span>ANY</span>do not<span>all</span>have to be satisifed at once. Only<span>one</span>condition must be satisfied for the email to send.</p>\r\n<p>As in our example above, if a customer matches<span>ANY</span>of the conditions<em>is in the segment ''US Customers''</em>or<em>in the segment ''AU Customers''</em>the email will be sent if the customer matches either of these conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Conditions you can use</h3>\r\n<p>You can use a variety of filters when targeting your campaigns. Here''s a list of each option:</p>\r\n<p><span>Has previously triggered:</span>Target customers that have previously triggered a specific event, e.g. Completed checkout a certain number of times.</p>\r\n<p><span>Doesn''t trigger:</span>Target customers that do not trigger a follow-up event within a specific period.</p>\r\n<p><span>Has user property:</span>Target users with a specific user attribute equal to / containing / not equal to / etc. a particular value, e.g. Age is less than 25</p>\r\n<p><span>Has event property:</span>Vero allows you to track customer attributes alongside events. You can use these attributes to filter specific campaigns, e.g Special offer is equal to Appsumo.</p>\r\n<p><span>Has received this email:</span>Ensure customers only receive a specific campaign once in their lifetime or over a specific period. In this way you can ensure customers are not receiving duplicate emails on a regular basis.</p>\r\n<p><span>Has been tagged:</span>You can tag customers with any custom tag you want. This allows you to do all sorts of filtering on large numbers of account, e.g. Email customers tagged with VIP. Tags can also be updated manually via the Vero people dashboard.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="highlight"><h5>DID YOU KNOW?</h5>\r\n<p>It''s best to use segments wherever you can when creating behavioral email campaigns. Segments help keep things nice and organised and give you a lot more power. Learn how to<a href="https://www.getvero.com/docs/create-a-segment">create a segment</a>.</p></div>', 'Behavioral Email Campaigns', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'behavioral-email-campaigns', '', '', '2014-07-05 06:48:31', '2014-07-05 06:48:31', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=help_docs&#038;p=73', 0, 'help_docs', '', 0),
(74, 3, '2014-07-05 06:49:23', '2014-07-05 06:49:23', '<p>Transactional emails are notifications that are are sent to customers when they take a specific, system critical action. These are usually emails such as password notifications, receipts or customer-to-customer updates.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Creating a transactional email</h3>\r\n<p>Creating a transactional email is identical to<a href="https://www.getvero.com/docs/behavioral-email-campaigns">creating a behavioral email campaign</a>. The only difference is the way transactional campaigns are handled by Vero.</p>\r\n<p>Newsletters and behavioral emails are<span>marketing emails.</span>If a customer unsubscribes they will no longer receive either of these two campaign types, as they have chosen to opt-out.</p>\r\n<p>In contrast, a transactional email is not a marketing email. It is an email sent in relation to a specific action that affects your customer. It is an email they need to receive in order to conduct business with you.</p>\r\n<p>For this reason, transactional emails<span>ignore unsubscribes.</span></p>\r\n<p>To create a transactional email, simply follow the steps used to create a behavioral campaign but ensure you mark the email as transactional.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/emails/transactional-9cb7b4258cc247bc5a9876e0083d4100.png" alt="Transactional" /></p>\r\n<p>On the campaign dashboard, you can quickly see transactional emails that are denoted with this tag.<img src="https://www.getvero.com/assets/docs/emails/transactional-dashboard-5dfb931a2da0951adcb5ea3c8834e67c.png" alt="Transactional-dashboard" /></p>\r\n\r\n<div class="highlight"><h5>DID YOU KNOW?</h5>\r\n<p>Transactional emails are prioritised so they are guaranteed immediately delivery. Whilst all campaigns are sent as quickly as possible, there is built in redundancy to ensure customers get mission-critical transactional emails instantly.</p></div>', 'Transactional Email Campaigns', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'transactional-email-campaigns', '', '', '2014-07-05 06:49:28', '2014-07-05 06:49:28', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=help_docs&#038;p=74', 0, 'help_docs', '', 0);
