(357, 23, '2015-02-06 06:10:07', '2015-02-06 06:10:07', 'By default, Vero will send your emails using our own IP addresses and domain configuration.\n\nFor many customers, this is totally fine, but you may want to send emails from your own domain instead.\n\nThe key benefits of this are: better deliverability, links and images are masked with your own domain and Vero is truly invisible to your customers.\n<h3>How your emails look by default</h3>\nWhen you first sign up to Vero, your emails will look something like this:\n\n<a href="https://www.getvero.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/via-getvero.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-358 size-full" src="https://www.getvero.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/via-getvero.png" alt="via-getvero" width="949" height="130" /></a>\n\nEmail clients will show this because the domain you send from (<em>test@chrishexton.com</em> in theexample above) does not match the sending domain, <em>getvero.com</em>.\n\n[help_highlight title="MULTIPLE FROM DOMAINS" text="You might see ''via getveromail.com'' or another domain as we use multiple domains to ensure maximum deliverability for all our customers."]\n\nBy setting up your Vero DNS records your recipients will no longer see the ''via'' message.\n<h3>Request your DNS records</h3>\nTo find the DNS records you need to setup for your domain, login to Vero and select the Account menu at the top right.\n\nFrom here, visit the Mail Providers tab. Ensure you have Use Vero as your email provider selected and click the Request DNS Records button:\n\n<a href="https://www.getvero.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/request.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-359" src="https://www.getvero.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/request.png" alt="request" width="437" height="227" /></a>\n\nYou will then need to set these DNS records up on your domain.\n\n[help_highlight title="TELL US YOUR DOMAIN" text="To request your DNS records you need to tell Vero which domain you will be sending from. You can define this under the Account &gt; Project Details."]\n\nTo do this, you''ll need to look at the how-to for your specific web host. Googling <a href="https://www.google.com.au/search?q=how+to+configure+dns+records&amp;oq=how+to+configure+dns+records" target="_blank">Setup DNS records</a> is the fastest way to find your providers instructions.\n<h3>Verify your records</h3>\nOnce you have added the DNS records to your domain, return to Vero and select the <strong>Configuration &gt;Account &gt; Email Providers</strong> menu. You will see the <em>Verify DNS Records</em> button.\n\nWhen you click this button Vero will check toconfirm that the DNS records are set up correctly and, if so,it will start sending your emails with this configuration going forward.\n\n<a href="https://www.getvero.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/verify.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-360" src="https://www.getvero.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/verify.png" alt="verify" width="484" height="335" /></a>\n\nFrom now on you will no longer see the''via'' message in your outgoing emails.', 'How to setup my domain signing and remove via getveromail.com from your emails', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'how-to-setup-my-domain-signing-and-remove-via-getveromail-com-from-your-emails', '', '', '2015-02-06 06:10:07', '2015-02-06 06:10:07', '', 0, 'https://www.getvero.com/?post_type=help_docs&amp;p=357', 0, 'help_docs', '', 0),
