(6446, 3, '2015-10-21 04:00:19', '2015-10-21 04:00:19', '<h2>Brand-spankin'' new.</h2>\r\nWe hatched an idea recently to use <i>scoping</i> to improve our conversion tracking. You can use the <i>scope_by</i> function to trigger emails based on event attributes, not just events. This means you can get more specific and your analytics will be more accurate. #Winning!\r\n\r\nWeb-hook yourself some line-caught variations. Unlike the fish that got away, you''ll now be able to see exactly which variation each open, click, bounce, etc. belongs to on our webhooks. We include the variation name, like Variation A for you. <a href="http://help.getvero.com/articles/setting-up-veros-webhooks.html">Read more about the webhooks here.</a>\r\n<h2>Dust off the wings.</h2>\r\nWe''ve patched up a dead end whereby requests using our <a href="http://www.getvero.com/external-attributes/">External Attributes</a> functionality were returning the Ruby error Undefined variable <i>nil</i> if your feed did not return valid JSON. Now, it will return the more readable, and useful, error message <i>"External attributes: output of #{@url} is not a Hash"</i>.\r\n\r\nTimezone management for newsletters plays fairly now. In the yesteryears of last week, if you sent a huge newsletter and there was a delay on a single timezone  say, GMT-4  it would push back the sends for GMT-5, GMT-6, etc. Now, newsletters are queued in batches at the exact time for each block of users, and sent round robin. Basically, the 1,200 people in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niue">Niue</a> (GMT+12) won''t be penalised for <a href="http://www.lonelyplanet.com/niue">choosing to live in paradise</a> .\r\n\r\nWe also released a bunch of garbage collectors to help us manage some memory leaks in our backend workers. Better workers means a more performant Vero all around, so we''ll keep hunting, like Elmer Fudd on Bugs Bunny.', 'Release v5.0 (8548c7f)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'release-v5-0-8548c7f', '', '', '2015-10-21 08:00:17', '2015-10-21 08:00:17', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?post_type=changelogs&#038;p=6446', 0, 'changelogs', '', 0),
